England call-up Simon Shaw arrived here on  Monday after lock Martin Johnson was ruled out of the rest of the South  African tour.
Johnson, punched in the defeat against Transvaal, will have a brain scan  to assess the injury. It is the second time in a year that the 24-year-old has  been concussed.
Shaw, 20, is 6ft 9ins and plays for Bristol. He is expected to play  against South Africa A on Tuesday.
